description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Surrey Downs Health and Care (SDHC)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;First Contact Practitioner (FCP)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full-time: 37.5 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 7&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SDHC is a dynamic partnership of Primary Care, Community and Acute colleagues at the forefront of delivering services locally to meet our patient needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a dynamic and forward thinking FCP to join our team in SDHC working in the ICP PCN Community Hub and SDHC physiotherapy team. This is an exciting new initiative and close working with the GPs and wider MSK pathway to fully integrate the service is an essential part of the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be the first point of contact for patients with musculoskeletal conditions and will be responsible for triaging them into the most appropriate pathway. This may be to self-care; to yourself for further assessment or FCP/Advanced Practitioner colleague; to community physiotherapy ; for appropriate diagnostics or to secondary care. You will also be expected to support the local community physiotherapy team hub.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have excellent clinical assessment and triage skills; be a great communicator, have good motivational skills and be happy to step out of your comfort zone to drive forward rapid changes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be self-motivating, organised, computer literate and able to demonstrate excellent interpersonal skills with a commitment to continued personal development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be development opportunities in line with the Health Education England recommendations for First Contact Practitioner and Advanced Practitioners in Primary Care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will be based in the Epsom area between GP surgeries and a community physiotherapy site and you must be able to meet the travel requirements of this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Sarah Runton&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: MSK Project Manager-SDHC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 07507 643128&lt;/p&gt;
